{"type":"message","id":"b0cb936d","parentId":"bc32dfbe","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:55:45.502Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_a4g94jr1q5v9_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 4893\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3557\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 045515 - The TIC experiment requires classifying pulse content as invariant (persistent patterns) vs variant (unique to specific pulse). I need to first examine existing pulse logs to understand their structure and extract features for classification.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"quick-river","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 4893\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=3557\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] the\r\n[mutation proposed] the\r\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 045515 - The TIC experiment requires classifying pulse content as invariant (persistent patterns) vs variant (unique to specific pulse). I need to first examine existing pulse logs to understand their structure and extract features for classification.\r\n","name":"pwsh C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774342545500}}
{"type":"message","id":"1bbd36bf","parentId":"b0cb936d","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:55:45.505Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_a4g94jr1q5v9_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 045413\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLooking at the goals, I need to advance the Phase 1 TIC Experiment. The next action is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on pulse log files.\r\n\r\nThe insight is that compression and causal discovery are the same problem - finding invariant structure across pulses.\r\n\r\nLet me implement a TIC classifier script that:\r\n1. Reads recent pulse logs (last 20)\r\n2. Identifies invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Attempts to predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n4. Measures classification accuracy\r\n\r\nI'll create a Python script for this experiment in the `src/` directory.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment is ready to be implemented - the insight that causal structure IS invariant structure provides a concrete testable hypothesis. The pulse logs are available for analysis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate TIC classifier script that analyzes pulse logs for invariant/variant content and validates the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n- Identifies invariant vs variant content across pulse logs\r\n- Attempts next-pulse prediction from invariants\r\n- Success criteria: >70% classification, >60% prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom datetime import datetime\r\n\r\nLOGS_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nMIN_LOGS = 5\r\n\r\ndef extract_text_features(text: str) -> dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract features that indicate invariant vs variant content.\"\"\"\r\n    features = {\r\n        \"word_count\": len(text.split()),\r\n        \"line_count\": len(text.splitlines()),\r\n        \"has_date\": bool(re.search(r'\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}', text)),\r\n        \"has_time\": bool(re.search(r'\\d{6}', text)),\r\n        \"has_file_path\": bool(re.search(r'[\\w/]+\\.\\w+', text)),\r\n        \"has_code\": bool(re.search(r'```|`.*`', text)),\r\n        \"has_bullet\": text.strip().startswith((\"-\", \"*\", \"•\")),\r\n        \"caps_ratio\": sum(1 for c in text if c.isupper()) / max(len(text), 1),\r\n    }\r\n    return features\r\n\r\ndef classify_content(text: str, prev_text: str = \"\") -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Classify content as INVARIANT (causal structure) or VARIANT (ephemeral).\"\"\"\r\n    features = extract_text_features(text)\r\n    prev_features = extract_text_features(prev_text) if prev_text else features\r\n    \r\n    # Invariant indicators: structure, patterns, architecture, goals\r\n    invariant_keywords = [\r\n        \"architecture\", \"hypothesis\", \"synthesis\", \"algorithm\",\r\n        \"phase\", \"goal\", \"insight\", \"theorem\", \"principle\",\r\n        \"compress\", \"causal\", \"invariant\", \"structure\", \"model\"\r\n    ]\r\n    \r\n    # Variant indicators: timestamps, specific values, ephemeral details\r\n    variant_keywords = [\r\n        \"timestamp\", \"created\", \"modified\", \"pulse_\", \r\n        \"duration\", \"seconds\", \"now\", \"current time\"\r\n    ]\r\n    \r\n    text_lower = text.lower()\r\n    invariant_score = sum(1 for kw in invariant_keywords if kw in text_lower)\r\n    variant_score = sum(1 for kw in variant_keywords if kw in text_lower)\r\n    \r\n    # Heuristic: structural elements are invariant\r\n    if features[\"has_code\"] and invariant_score > 0:\r\n        return \"INVARIANT\"\r\n    if features[\"has_bullet\"] and features[\"word_count\"] > 10:\r\n        return \"INVARIANT\"\r\n    if invariant_score > variant_score + 1:\r\n        return \"INVARIANT\"\r\n    if variant_score > invariant_score:\r\n        return \"VARIANT\"\r\n    \r\n    # Check for repeated patterns with prev\r\n    if prev_text and text[:50] == prev_text[:50]:\r\n        return \"INVARIANT\"\r\n    \r\n    return \"VARIANT\"\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariants: list, current: str) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse content based on invariant structure.\"\"\"\r\n    # Simple prediction: next pulse continues invariant patterns\r\n    invariant_text = \" \".join(invariants)\r\n    \r\n    if \"hypothesis\" in invariant_text.lower():\r\n        return \"continuation\"\r\n    if \"architecture\" in invariant_text.lower():\r\n        return \"refinement\"\r\n    if \"phase\" in invariant_text.lower():\r\n        return \"progression\"\r\n    \r\n    return \"unknown\"\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Run TIC experiment on pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\r\n    print(\"TIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression\")\r\n    print(\"Hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\")\r\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\r\n    \r\n    # Collect pulse logs\r\n    log_files = sorted(LOGS_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), key=os.path.getmtime, reverse=True)\r\n    \r\n    if len(log_files) < MIN_LOGS:\r\n        print(f\"ERROR: Need at least {MIN_LOGS} logs, found {len(log_files)}\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    # Use last 20 logs\r\n    logs_to_analyze = log_files[:20]\r\n    print(f\"\\nAnalyzing {len(logs_to_analyze)} pulse logs...\")\r\n    \r\n    all_classifications = []\r\n    invariant_content = []\r\n    prev_text = \"\"\r\n    \r\n    for i, log_file in enumerate(reversed(logs_to_analyze)):\r\n        content = log_file.read_text()\r\n        classification = classify_content(content, prev_text)\r\n        \r\n        all_classifications.append({\r\n            \"log\": log_file.name,\r\n            \"classification\": classification\r\n        })\r\n        \r\n        if classification == \"INVARIANT\":\r\n            invariant_content.append(content[:200])\r\n        \r\n        prev_text =\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 04:54:41\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774342545502}}
